    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>Though ἀθέμιτος may be regarded as meaning literally ‘pertaining to what is not allowed’ ({D:13.144}), it acquires by association not only the meaning of lawless (a meaning which is possibly applicable to {S:06000400300038}) but also disgusting or wanton in connection with idol worship. Such a semantic development is typical of what often happens when meanings shift from an objective to a subjective orientation.</Content>
